                                 <div></div> 
                                 <div class="text-container galileo-ap-content-editor">
                                  <div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px;">Dear parents and guardians,</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 14px;">Governor Cuomo just announced that schools will be closed an additional two weeks, after which time he will assess the situation. This will keep City School District of New Rochelle schools closed beyond the Spring Break.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;">We know many members of the community remain anxious about school closures. The CSDNR will provide you with timely updates as we receive them.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 14px;">The CSDNR is committed to ensuring that our Distance Learning Plan supports students through closures, excluding Spring Break, April 6 through 10. During the break, we urge you to rest, rejuvenate and spend time spent with family.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 14px;">We will continue our food distribution services at all of our distribution locations through the Spring Break for those who depend upon school breakfast and lunches. We know free school meals matter.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div> 
                                    <span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 14px;">The CSDNR remains committed to educating students and ensuring that they have access to healthy and balanced nutrition. We continue to provide Chromebooks to middle and high school students which can be picked up at the high school Monday through Friday 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. Please ensure that you have a form filled out. If you require a form please email </span>
                                    <a href="mailto:chromebook@nredlearn.org" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: underline;">chromebook@nredlearn.org</a>
                                    <span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 14px;">. Chromebooks will not be distributed during the Spring Break; distribution after the break will resume April 13, 2020.</span> 
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Thank you,</span>
                                   </div> 
                                  </div>
